2–June 1555":"1492–June 1555","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1512–1577":"1512–1577","1515–1575":"1515–1575","1520–1549":"1520–1549","1537–1607":"1537–1607","1492–1555":"1492–1555","28 April 1549":"28 April 1549","1492":"1492","16 Jun 1555":"16 June 1555","June 1555":"June 1555","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1555":"1555","1577":"1577","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","about 1512":"about 1512","1497":"1497","about 1511":"about 1511","1607":"1607","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","1537":"1537","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England","Winston, Suffolk, England":"Winston, Suffolk, England","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":57,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born in 1492, in Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married John Wylie about 1511, in Thorley, Hertfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in June 1555, in Thorley, Hertfordshire, England, at the age of 63, and was buried in Thorley, Hertfordshire, England."},"et":{"1492–June 1555":"1492–juuni 1555","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1512–1577":"1512–1577","1515–1575":"1515–1575","1520–1549":"1520–1549","1537–1607":"1537–1607","1492–1555":"1492–1555","28 April 1549":"28. aprill 1549","1492":"1492","16 Jun 1555":"16. juuni 1555","June 1555":"juuni 1555","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1555":"1555","1577":"1577","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","about 1512":"umbes 1512","1497":"1497","about 1511":"umbes 1511","1607":"1607","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","1537":"1537","Chelmsford, Essex, England":"Chelmsford, Essex, England","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England":"Bishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, England","Winston, Suffolk, England":"Winston, Suffolk, England","Thorley, Hertfordshire, England":"Thorley, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1492–June 1555":"1492–kesäkuu 1555","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1512–1577":"1512–1577","1515–1575":"1515–1575","1520–1549":"1520–1549","1537–1607":"1537–1607","1492–1555":"1492–1555","28 April 1549":"28. huhtikuuta 1549","1492":"1492","16 Jun 1555":"16. kesäkuuta 1555","June 1555":"kesäkuu 1555","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1555":"1555","1577":"1577","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","about 1512":"noin 1512","1497":"1497","about 1511":"noin 1511","1607":"1607","1549":"1549","1515":"151